# Data Catalog — Luminae Beauty (Gold Layer)

## Overview
This data catalog documents the **Gold Layer (Star Schema)** for the *Luminae Beauty Omni-Channel Marketing & Sales Analytics* project.

The Gold Layer is **analytics-ready**, built on top of cleaned Silver layer data, and is structured into:
- **Dimension tables** (context: campaign, product, date, source)
- **Fact tables** (measurable performance: orders, marketing, web events)

---

# DIMENSION TABLES

---

##  `gold.dim_date`

**Purpose:** Standardized calendar dimension used across all fact tables for time-based analysis.

| Column Name | Data Type | Description |
|-------------|----------|-------------|
| date_key | INT | Surrogate key in YYYYMMDD format (e.g., 20260131) |
| full_date | DATE | Actual calendar date |
| year_int | INT | Year extracted from date |
| month_name | VARCHAR | Full month name (e.g., January) |
| month_int | INT | Month number (1–12) |
| weekday_int | INT | Day of week (1–7 depending on SQL server settings) |
| is_weekend | BIT / INT | Flag indicating weekend (1 = weekend, 0 = weekday) |

---

##  `gold.dim_campaign_name`

**Purpose:** Standardized marketing campaign dimension across all channels (Email, Meta, Google).

| Column Name | Data Type | Description |
|-------------|----------|-------------|
| campaign_key | INT | Surrogate key generated via HASH (CHECKSUM) |
| raw_campaign_name | VARCHAR | Original campaign name from source systems |
| standard_campaign_name | VARCHAR | Normalized campaign grouping (e.g., Newsletter, Flash Sale) |
| campaign_objective | VARCHAR | Business goal classification (brand_awareness, conversions, traffic) |
| source_platform | VARCHAR | Platform source (Email, Meta, Google) |
| start_date | DATE | First observed date of campaign activity |
| end_date | DATE | Last observed date of campaign activity |

---

##  `gold.dim_products`

**Purpose:** Product hierarchy and categorization for ecommerce analytics.

| Column Name | Data Type | Description |
|-------------|----------|-------------|
| product_key | INT | Surrogate product identifier (HASH of SKU + name) |
| product_sku | VARCHAR | Stock Keeping Unit identifier |
| product_name | VARCHAR | Product name |
| category | VARCHAR | Product category (Serums, Moisturisers, Toners, Skincare) |

---

##  `gold.dim_sources`

**Purpose:** Web traffic source classification for attribution and channel analysis.

| Column Name | Data Type | Description |
|-------------|----------|-------------|
| source_key | INT | Surrogate key (HASH of source attributes) |
| source_name | VARCHAR | Traffic source (e.g., google, facebook) |
| medium | VARCHAR | Marketing medium (e.g., cpc, organic, email) |
| channel_grouping | VARCHAR | High-level channel grouping |
| device_type | VARCHAR | Device category (mobile, desktop, tablet) |

---

#  FACT TABLES

---

##  `gold.fact_marketing_performance`

**Purpose:** Unified marketing performance metrics across Google Ads, Meta Ads, and Email.

| Column Name | Data Type | Description |
|-------------|----------|-------------|
| campaign_key | INT | Foreign key to `dim_campaign_name` |
| date_key | INT | Foreign key to `dim_date` (YYYYMMDD) |
| channel_source | VARCHAR | Marketing channel (Google, Meta, Email) |
| spend | DECIMAL / FLOAT | Total advertising spend |
| impressions | INT | Number of ad impressions |
| clicks | INT | Number of clicks |
| platform_attributed_revenue | DECIMAL / FLOAT | Revenue attributed to platform activity |

---

## `gold.fact_orders`

**Purpose:** Ecommerce order-level transactional fact table.

| Column Name | Data Type | Description |
|-------------|----------|-------------|
| order_line_id | INT | Surrogate row identifier (window function generated) |
| order_id | VARCHAR | Cleaned order identifier |
| date_key | INT | Foreign key to `dim_date` |
| product_key | INT | Foreign key to `dim_products` |
| campaign_key | INT | Foreign key to `dim_campaign_name` |
| customer_id | VARCHAR | Unique customer identifier |
| order_status | VARCHAR | Status of order (completed, cancelled, etc.) |
| quantity | INT | Units purchased |
| unit_price_gbp | DECIMAL | Price per unit in GBP |
| net_revenue | DECIMAL | Total order value (GBP) |
| is_new_customer | BIT / INT | Flag for first-time customer |
| attributed_channel | VARCHAR | Channel attribution |
| attributed_source | VARCHAR | Source attribution |

---

##  `gold.fact_web_events`

**Purpose:** Website behavioral analytics at session/event level.

| Column Name | Data Type | Description |
|-------------|----------|-------------|
| event_id | INT | Surrogate event identifier |
| session_id | VARCHAR | Web session identifier |
| date_key | INT | Foreign key to `dim_date` |
| campaign_key | INT | Foreign key to `dim_campaign_name` |
| source_key | INT | Foreign key to `dim_sources` |
| user_id | VARCHAR | Anonymous or logged-in user ID |
| landing_page | VARCHAR | First page visited in session |
| country | VARCHAR | User geographic location |
| new_vs_returning | VARCHAR | User type classification |
| pageviews | INT | Number of pages viewed |
| sessions | INT | Session count |
| bounce | BIT / INT | Bounce indicator (1 = bounced) |
| time_on_site_secs | INT | Time spent on site in seconds |
| converted | BIT / INT | Conversion flag |
| order_value_gbp | DECIMAL | Revenue generated from session |

---

#  Notes on Design
- All **fact tables use surrogate keys** from dimensions for consistency and performance.
- `date_key` uses **YYYYMMDD integer format** for efficient joins.
- Campaign and product dimensions use **HASH-based surrogate keys (CHECKSUM)**.
- Schema follows a **Star Schema model optimized for BI tools (Power BI, Tableau, Looker)**.

---

#  Key KPIs Supported
- ROAS (Return on Ad Spend)
- CPA (Cost per Acquisition)
- AOV (Average Order Value)
- Conversion Rate
- Revenue attribution by channel & campaign
- Customer acquisition trends
